name: Lt. Governor Peggy Flanagan
tweet: Thank you to the advocates who worked to pass the reauthorization of the Violence Against Women Act, and to @POTUS, an original sponsor of VAWA in 1994, for signing the bill. It shouldn’t take this much effort to protect the lives and safety of women, but I’m grateful it’s done.

name: Lt. Governor Peggy Flanagan
tweet: Today marks a year since the shooting in Atlanta that took the lives of eight people, including Asian women. We continue to mourn and honor their lives. Our state stands against the hateful rhetoric and violence against the Asian community today and every day.

tweet: It’s #EqualPayDay, marking how far into the year women must work to earn the same as a man in a year. And still, many Black, Native, and women of color have to work longer into the year to catch up.   This is simply unacceptable – everyone deserves to be paid a fair wage.
